<span id="freeTextContainer17413968211426880301">What is there to add to the universal praise for Rachel Carson? This book isn&apos;t a walk in the park, and it&apos;s crammed with (accesible) Scientific data, but it changed the world. <br/><br/>I was more fascinated by Carson&apos;s rhetoric than in her findings, which are now more than 45 years old. I read this book to learn how she built a case that challenged every major scientific, political and corporate institution in the country. And she did it by connecting with the shared values of average Americans. Bravo, </span>
  <span id="freeText17413968211426880301" style="display:none">What is there to add to the universal praise for Rachel Carson? This book isn't a walk in the park, and it's crammed with (accesible) Scientific data, but it changed the world. <br /><br />I was more fascinated by Carson's rhetoric than in her findings, which are now more than 45 years old. I read this book to learn how she built a case that challenged every major scientific, political and corporate institution in the country. And she did it by connecting with the shared values of average Americans. Bravo, Rachel!</span>
